<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,566,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,466,710,737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Diagnostic characters:</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[593,746,711,737]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,746,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed by a combination of characters in male genitalia: gnathos medially arched backward or produced into a process, with a process from base of each arm produced in most species and covered with thick and short setae; valva rhomboidal, usually with a process at base, costa with an apical spine; vesica with single cornutus or in form of bunch of spines (
<bibRefCitation author="Rong, H. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Li, H." box="[951,1145,819,845]" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" pagination="159 - 174" refId="ref5769" refString="Rong, H., Wang, Y. &amp; Li, H. (2017) Review of the genus Termioptycha Meyrick, 1889 (Lepidoptera, Pyralidae) from China, with descriptions of four new species. Zootaxa, 4329 (2), 159 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4329.2.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Rong 
<emphasis box="[1021,1070,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="416" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,566,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,854,880]" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Due to presence of an apical spine on the costa of valva, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[954,1107,855,881]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[954,1107,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyrick, 1890" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Lepidogma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Lepidogma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[191,358,891,917]" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" pagination="429 - 492" refId="ref5439" refString="Meyrick, E. (1890) On the classification of the Pyralidina of the European fauna. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1890, 429 - 492, pl. 15. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1890. tb 02704. x" type="journal article" year="1890">Meyrick, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the specific shape of gnathos distinguishes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[957,1110,891,917]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1110,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" box="[1176,1302,891,917]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Lepidogma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1302,891,917]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Lepidogma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Externally, the members of 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" box="[340,532,927,953]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Teliphasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[340,448,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Teliphasa</emphasis>
Moore
</taxonomicName>
also resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[802,955,927,953]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[802,955,927,953]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, the conspicuously sub-rounded valva and lack of costal spine in male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" box="[713,821,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Teliphasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[713,821,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Teliphasa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1889" box="[1138,1291,963,989]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Termioptycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1291,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="416">Termioptycha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
